column1: # SOURCE: Synthetic data generated for Community Agri-PV project
# DESCRIPTION: Daily weather data for Sinai Peninsula

# LOGIC: Temperature uses sinusoidal annual cycle + AR(1) year anomaly + daily noise. Solar uses latitude-based seasonal variation. Wind uses spring-peak seasonal pattern with gamma-distributed noise. Precipitation uses rare events (exponential) concentrated Nov-Feb.
# ASSUMPTIONS: Hot arid desert climate (BWh Koppen). Summer max 38-46C
column2: winter max 18-26C. Annual rainfall 20-80mm. Solar summer 6-8 kWh/m2/day
column3: winter 3-5 kWh/m2/day. Wind 2-6 m/s average with occasional gusts to 12 m/s.
